New Features and Important Changes in ctools 1.0.0

Author(s) : Juergen Knoedlseder

20 February 2015


1. Introduction
---------------
This document briefly summarizes executable by executable the most important
changes made since the last release of ctools. The code complies to GammaLib
version 1.0.0 or above.


2. Configuration
-----------------
None


3. Python interface
-------------------
The ctools module does no longer import automatically Python scripts. This
prevents to break the ctools interface in case that some dependencies in
the scripts are broken. Scripts (such as obsutils, analysisutils or plotutils)
are support scripts that may not be fully supported throughout the
development. They may be moved into a special contributions area in the future.


4. Support model
----------------
None


5. ctobssim - CTA observation simulation
----------------------------------------
None


6. ctselect - CTA event selection
---------------------------------
If INDEF, UNDEF, NONE or UNDEFINED are passed for the selection parameters, no
selection will be performed.


7. ctbin - CTA event binning
